records.addlTxt:
The State moves to delete the weapon enhancer on count 1.  Motion granted.
GUILTY plea entered to the amended charge of possess THC with intent to deliver.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 and 3.  Motion granted.
The Court has reviewed both the sentencing memorandum and the letter from the State and orders these documents sealed.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of seven (7) years.  That is three (3) years initial confinement followed by four (4) years extended supervision.  Execution of sentence is stayed and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for five (5) years.
The Court finds the defendant not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program, but eligible for the Earned Release Program.
Conditions of probation:
1) Spend eight (8) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing on 04-29-15 at 8:30 a.m.  Court authorizes transfer to Fond Du Lac County Jail;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
4) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) Pay court costs;
6) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) maintain fulltime employment;
8) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same.
If revoked, the defendant has credit for 23 days.  (06-09-14 to 07-02-14)
The $15,000.00 cash bail on file is to be applied to court costs.  The balance of $14,482.00 is returned to Lynn Whitmore by check instruction no: CR 60.
Check instruction.
Minutes.
